---
title: 'Glass and Bone'
date: '2026-03-05'
category: 'poetry'
excerpt: 'On being both fragile and stubborn at once'
---

I am made of glass and bone —
one half shatters clean,
the other refuses.

People mistake the glass for weakness.
They don't understand
that it takes more courage
to be breakable
than to pretend
you are not.

The bone holds what the glass cannot.
The glass shows what the bone hides.

Together they make something
that neither softness nor hardness
could build alone.

---
### Expressions
- **"shatters clean"** — clean breaks are honest. Messy ones mean you were holding on.
- **"courage to be breakable"** — vulnerability isn't weakness. Choosing to stay open knowing you can break — that's the harder thing.
